reviews_data.review_text: This is still my favorite French/European cafe style place in Charlotte. The quality is always consistent, everyone working is very nice and pricing is not outrageous. They also have savory options if you’re wanting a light lunch or snack outside of the sweets.
We had some beautiful lattes at Chez Marie. Their macarons were also very fresh. We sat outside on an early Saturday morning, so not too much noise or traffic. We will definitely be back.

Wonderful atmosphere, feels like you’re in Europe. Staff were very friendly and greeted us and if we had any questions on the menu.
Started off with the Blue chai latte which was absolutely delicious, not too overpowering, just right.
The deserts were top tier treats. The Coconut mojito is packed with coconut and lime flavors. Very moist cake inside with a coconut moose jello like outer ring, topped with white chocolate. The Passion fruit cheesecake has a soft cheesecake texture with a big passion fruit flavor.
The Quiche Loraine had smoky ham pieces inside alongside a delicious gooey cheese. The only thing I would change is the crust because it was a bit too thick. The Le Picque-Nique had all fresh ingredients. A Crunchy toasted baguette with smoked ham and beautifully blended toppings. Doesn’t get any fresher than that.
Overall, Perfect spot for couples and a girls brunch or lunch. Definitely check them out!!!

Excelentes.
Super amables y delicioso.
Absolutely amazing authentic pastries, if you haven't been you must try it and if you've tried it I know you're going back again

I loved it, I recommend it
I love it here! Excellent service, will be coming back soon
I love the desserts here. All the food is delicious. They also have excellent service... highly recommended!

An amazing spot!
Has delicious desserts and cakes 👏🏼
Beautiful place and good service

I went today with my family and the attention was incredible, the atmosphere very pleasant, the staff very attentive. I loved the variety of options they had. I recommend the Pain chocolate and the pistachio paris brest are the best I've tried!

This place has terrible customer service. Beware if you are doing the afternoon tea that they will not accommodate dietary restrictions nor tell you what you will be getting. A member of our party has a severe nut allergy and informed the staff before she paid and was assured they would accommodate her. However, all food arrived together with many items with nuts. Nut free items were touching any items she could possibly eat. She requested to pay only for her tea since she could no longer have the food and was told no. The manager was very combative to talk to and it took a significant amount of effort to be able to receive a refund (the manager told us it was our fault for not mentioning allergies and that any allergies we had were our responsibility—however the staff was told about allergies beforehand and still charged and ignored information that was provided beforehand) I would not recommend going here—the service is terrible and the food is below average for what you are paying for. There are much better cafes to spend your time and money in Charlotte with much better service.
My favorite cafe in town. Coffee is consistently good, pastries are superb and service is always friendly.

I was extremely disappointed in the service that my friend and I received when visiting this establishment. Immediately upon walking in we were not greeted or acknowledged in any way, shape or form. Which was a bit of a red flag, being that we found out about this place via TikTok and were super excited to visit. We still proceeded to the counter, which had 3 people in front of us (who looked as though they were in the same party). As we walked up to the counter and looked around for a paper menu, the workers still did not acknowledge our presence or say that they would be with us. This was another huge red flag after waiting for about 5 minutes to not only be acknowledged, but also assisted, we ended up leaving. We have no intention of ever coming back to this establishment.
Amazing experience. We bought many items and they were all mind blowing. The staff went above and beyond what we expected.
Cute little coffee shop with sweet pastries. Get there early, they sell out. Cute vibe to hang out or work.
Love this place!!!

Chez Marie is very small shop and there is not much space, but the issue is the energy inside the building. I was so anxious. The customers inside were being so rude to the employees and honestly it really ruined the experience for me. Would go back for the pastries.

Picked up a passion fruit tart for my wife for her birthday. It’s her favorite ! It’s a distance to go there but well worth it.

Chez Marie is the cutest bakery ever. The atmosphere is sophisticated but also calm and sweet. The mixed berry danish, Madelines and chai latte are my favorites. The staff is always super nice. I definitely recommend for a coffee date with friends !

reviews_data.review_text: Very lovely place. Great pâtisseries and atmosphere

This is a lovely bakery! It’s so bright and clean and welcoming. The pastries are very good. Sometimes you see something and you think, oh, it’ll be ok and it is. This was not one of those times! I chose a ham and cheese croissant. It was not the biggest or showiest pastry, but it was delicious. (Going to show me not to judge a book by its cover!) I took it to go, but it was so cute inside, it looked like a nice place to meet a friend or to work for a little bit.

I’ve been torn about posting this—part of me wants to give it 5 stars because it’s that good, but the other part wants to keep it a hidden gem. Selfishly, I’d rather not blow up the spot… but here we go.  Everything is amazing - trust me - I’ve tried it all.

Went 3 times within 2 days!
I loved the calm and classy atmosphere of this place. Tried the regular latte and ice latte, also their croissants, everything was very good.
The music selection is perfect for sitting and enjoying a good coffee by yourself of with company, sitting in a comfortable and yet beautiful couch.
The service was fantastic, everyone was nice and friendly every time I went.

I really like the pastries here but they’ve gotten lazy over the years. They used to have new items what seemed to be every week and they had much more variety of breads and pastries. Now it is rather baron in there

Beautiful, charming and simply delightful cafe w/ amazing authentic French desserts! Every bite was pure bliss! Drinks were strong and delicious as well.

Loved the gold accents on the decor and cutlery. The space is kept very clean and tidy as staff was actively seen cleaning each table and seat as guests departed. The young lady at the register was very polite, welcoming and patient as well.

This is truly a slice of Paris tucked away in Charlotte! From the moment you walk in, you’re greeted with the warmest smiles and the most inviting, cozy atmosphere. It feels like a little escape!

I was so impressed that I decided to place a special order for my bridal shower, and I’m so glad I did. Look at the photo attached! The assortment of pastries we received was beyond stunning, delicate, delicious, and absolutely beautiful. My girlfriends were astonished!

Maria and her team are so kind and passionate about what they do. You can tell how much love they put into every detail!!

This place is more than a bakery — it’s an experience. Whether you’re planning a celebration or just stopping by for a coffee and croissant, Chez Marie is worth every visit. It’s easily one of my favorite spots in Charlotte!

Love everything about this place! My favorite pastry place in Charlotte.  I think the danishes and quiche are our favorite but everything is delicious!  Love the decor…great ladies morning out place…cute and cozy.

This place has such neat little pastries, I can’t believe it’s local. I tried the chocolate coffee pie and the other fancy chocolate pastry with the chocolate ring—both were decadent. The server was super friendly. We went for the first time about an hour before close and only a few types of pastries remained, so I definitely recommend going earlier in the day for the best selection (pictured, from our second visit).

$17 for a stale danish and not even a 12 oz matcha that I had to go home and try to make it taste better and I dont think its ceremonial grade. I know its South Park but it should be at least good if your charging that much. I’ll keep going to tous le jours.

fantastic croissants and coffee!!
Nice staff, good pastries, clean and bright space. A little small so it will likely be crowded but if you can get a table it is a lovely place to enjoy a morning treat! Would definitely go back.
Cute little corner cafe with nice ambience and deliciously crafted drinks and pastries.

VERY DISAPPOINTED. I received very poor service from the three ladies behind the counter. I came in Wednesday morning 7/2 at 8:58 an and ordered 4 croissants to go. I was in a hurry, and didn’t pay much attention to the bill. When I got home, I checked my ApplePay and noticed they had cost $33 (~$8/pastry). I thought that was a bit expensive, and checked the website, where they were listed as $3.50 each. Even with a generous tip, I was charged about  $10 extra. I assumed it must have been a simple mistake, and went back ten minutes later. I explained the situation to the lady who had just checked me out. None of the ladies behind the counter seemed to speak much English, ( and didn’t respond to my Spanish) and told me the owner who I had chatted with 10 min prior was gone. There are several other very good French places in the area, and I will be going there in the future.
Ran in to grab coffee to go and ended up sitting for 30 minutes. We love this little cafe and their chai latte and lattes were so good!

I've lived in Charlotte for over 35 years and this is one of my favorite places ever.  The best croissant and iced coffee I've ever had.  The atmosphere is magical.  Also, the strawberry cheesecake is incredible.  all of the items are so intricately crafted--it is quite an experience.  Chez-Marie is a hidden gem.

Chez Marie is my favorite cafe ever!! The chocolate coffee tart is light yet rich, the texture is consistently smooth, not over-the-top coffee flavor! My second favorite: lemon meringue tart! The meringue is always perfectly toasted, the lemon filling is perfectly tart and sweet, it is the perfect balance. The crust is my favorite part!!

Came here after really wanting a professional grade pastry. This was it! It’s a beautiful cafe setting that captures Parisian style and Charlotte elegance. I took my 8yo daughter and she loved it. This place is a curated dream, so glad we came.
Very nice calm place
My favorite place for a coffe and a spectacular dessert in those days u want to share a family moment or closets one, no regrets of coming here anytime
Beautiful French café with the best bakery items. I tried the blue matcha and the pistachio bakery item and they were delicious!

First time. Run. Don't walk.

Chez Marie is a pretty solid French Patisserie. I got the opportunity to taste a large variety of the pastries they were selling that day and was impressed for the most part. The mixed berry entremet was my favorite thing that I tried: it was tart, light, and rich at the same time, while not being overly sweet. The chocolate entremet, while having a pretty presentation, was way too rich and was difficult to eat more than a couple of nibbles. The lemon tart was also pretty with the toasted meringue on it, however, it tasted a little too much like a key lime pie to me. All of the macaroons that I tried were good as well, with standouts being the raspberry and pistachio. The location is very nice in South Park near the OG Pancake House and has a pretty, delicate interior. The ladies working the front were also very nice. It seems they change what they are selling often, I will have to go back and check it out again sometime.

A great spot to feel like you’ve traveled outside of the states! Great atmosphere, beautiful and delicious pastries and coffee, and clean 👌 We ordered the pistachio French best, Black Forest emberet, and a vanilla latte. Everything was excellent! We came on a Sunday around 11am and we were able to get a table. Some weekends may be busier, but honestly we felt like it would be worth the wait ☺️
Fresh! Delicious. 😋 great taste.
The mixed berry danish was very hard, same as a few macaroons. Other than that, enjoyable and nice service.

This is a beautiful little bakery. They make great pastries, the closest I found in Charlotte to the real French ones. They used to make great croissants and pain au chocolat but lately they changed the recipe, I would say skip them and get the pastries.
They offer an array of drink options.
This spot is good hangout place for small groups (4). It is a small place that gets filled up quickly specially on weekends. The parking is free but can be tricky at times as this place is located in a small shopping area with other restaurants and a couple of stores - so plan accordingly.

I got a Togo order and there were not many option’s. One of the waitresses made a comment to another with an eye roll when an eat in customer asked for more water for her tea. This pastry shop is a small gem! Tucked in a shopping center right across from Southpark Mall. Perfect for a sweet or savory treat after shopping. There are a lot of stores so parking can be a little crowded. I ordered a cheese danish, croissant, and a tiramisu macaron. Everything was fresh. My favorite was the cheese danish..it was the best danish I’ve had. Buttery, flaky, perfect cheese to pastry ratio. Definitely will visit again. Price tag $13 not including tip.

What an amazing little shop! I have a friend who keeps talking abt them so I finally got my chance to check it out. It’s very small and intimate in there and not much seating but fortunately we were able to find some once a group left. I ordered the London fog, smoked ham sandwich and a cheese danish. Everything was positivity delish. That danish was literally the best I’ve ever had. This place is definitely a must try, and believe me I will be back over and over again.

Great coffee, real fresh baguettes, and a wonderful ambience.

Nice place, but a bit small, so it gets crowded. Food and drinks were delicious. My chai latte was spot on - the right amount of sweetness. Staff was friendly and polite. A good experience, will come again.

I was very excited to go there to eat, I read several reviews of the place and it is just as described, a very nice atmosphere and good customer service and the food was delicious, I hope to go there again with my friends!
The place is very nice,even though I did not stay.The Pastries are very good.

Great place! I recently had the pleasure of dining at Chez Marie Patisserie, and it was a delightful experience! The moment I walked in, I was greeted by the heavenly aroma of freshly baked goods and the charming, cozy atmosphere. I started with a buttery croissant that was perfectly flaky and golden. For dessert, I couldn’t resist trying their signature macarons, which were exquisite—soft, colorful, and filled with rich flavors. I also enjoyed a slice of their decadent chocolate cake, which was rich and moist, a true indulgence. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, eager to help with recommendations. Overall, Chez Marie Patisserie is a must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth or looking for a cozy spot to enjoy delicious pastries. I can't wait to go back and try more of their delectable treats!

reviews_data.review_text: I went for a little afternoon snack and coffee. Everything was delicious. Nice place. All the pastries were very fresh and delicious. The cappuccino was perfect as well as the blue matcha.
Very tasty cute place .

We were really excited this visit this place.  We did not realize It was located in a very crowded shopping plaza, so the parking lot was almost full.  There is a front patio to sit on which was great because we had our dog with us.  My hubby ordered for us and I really wanted the Cheese Danish but they were sold out.  So we picked 2 different desserts and coffee.

The desserts were good, kind of sweet for me but the presentation was beautiful.  The coffee was ok, it seemed like more foam than coffee.  Again, I loved the presentation of the coffee.

The service was great and the waitress was very kind.  The price was a little expensive for 2 desserts and 2 coffees.  With a tip it was $32.00.

Sitting on the patio was nothing fancy as you are looking at a bunch of cars in a parking lot.

I am glad we visited this place as it’s always nice to try new places.

I almost don’t want to write this review because this place is such a gem—I’d hate to see it get too crowded! But honestly, the croissants here are incredible—as authentic as any I’ve had in France. Everything I tried was absolutely delicious, and the coffee was fantastic too. This bakery truly feels like a little slice of Paris, and I can’t wait to come back. Highly recommend

reviews_data.review_text: I ended up only ordering 2 pastries to go as they are very expensive for their size. The lychee raspberry entremet was fantastic, and each layer was a delight and perfectly made. I would come back for another. The earl grey eclair however was a huge disappointment. It's very small, the glaze was rubbery, the filling was sparce, split, and curdled. For $8 I'm surprised they put them out like that. They really need to adjust their prices on some things or rework them to make them worth it.

First time visiting the bakery. It’s a small, quaint shop with limited seating. The croissant was delicious!

Me encanta su atención!
Everything was so delicious,Everything looks super clean, and costumer service is excellent

Excellent attention. I loved the macaroni and coffee.

This place has some interesting tasting coffee. I love the flavor. It was open I would have went over there but it's late Sunday. And I had to go over to the fake McDonald's just down the street.

Very expensive for the product. Everything has an excellent presentation and the desserts are good but too expensive. The caramel coffee was terrible and the chai latte tasted like hot milk with cinnamon.

We preordered through phone because we had a 2hr drive and we brought all the sweets for our family and we all enjoyed every dessert. Thank you for that experience. We will definitely be back for tea time with all our girls

Super cute place , friendly service and delicious French bakery good's.

Go for coffee or tea with treats, you won't be disappointed..

reviews_data.review_text: Атмосфера, сервис, обслуживание, десерты 10/10. Но снимаю одну звезду за кислый кофе( Для детей все предусмотрено и это огромный плюс, стульчики и туалетный столик имеется. Спасибо
After paying a bomb for a latte, i got one without any art on it and to top it all, not even that great. Plus macaroons were not good. Very few options of desserts.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are sorry you were dissatisfied with your experience at Chez Marie.

We believe that the value of our products that we offer is fairly estimated and it corresponds to the high quality of the ingredients we select and hard work we apply. 

We agree with your comment about the design on the latte, but we are currently training new people. We can reassure you that the quality of the drink remains the same as all of our baristas follow the same recipe. 

We wanted to make it right to you and served you a freshly made cappuccino upon your request free of charge, that you have also asked to be taken “to go”.

We make all our desserts daily and due to a high demand we run out of many items by the end of the day. Our customers can always call and place an advance order for a later pick up.

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious coffee made from beans roasted by Bristot in the Dolomites. The carrot cake was also delicious. Don't waste $7 on the baguette. No crust, very flabby, only good for toast.

Ohh la la. French and Fresh. I loved the intimate bright location. Gorgeous decor with vibrant esthetic.

I got the Blue Mattcha w/ Stevia (Iced). It's made with Lavender, and it's Sligh sweet with a beautiful aromatic.  It doesn't have anything to cut the deep dairy taste. However, I like milk so I wasn't disappointed. There's a borage of pastries to tempt you. I found the display gorgeous. I'm on no carbs right now, but they looked so enchanting.

My first timer!!  Cute danity lil french cafe i fell in love
My lunch was delicious. Friendly staff cute cafe. Surely i will be back!!!!!!
The greeter was rude and made us uncomfortable. Disappointing as I was really excited to try them.
Awesome
Cute little high end bakery
Beautiful and delicious pastries.
Love it here, great food and service
Love the ambience, the food was good.  The matcha coffee was the best. The service was excellent. Will definitely return. Every detail was thought of.
Stopped here on the way back home. Great cappuccino! and croissants!
I love this place! They have the best croissants. Coffee is also good.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Pastry Selection, Ham and Cheese Croissant

reviews_data.review_text: Good service and gluten free options. Quaint place. They bake the goods on-site. Slightly pricey, but as to be expected based on the location.

This patisserie never disappoints. The desserts are not only gorgeous, but also delicious!
Keep in mind it is a small place, and can be busy. Also, it is pricier than other patisseries around, but definitely worth it.

Food and service were great, the employees were super friendly but my partner and I had a very uncomfortable experience with the owner sitting in the cafe. When my partner put cash in the tip jar, she piped up in a snooty tone and said, “You know you don’t have to do that, this isn’t like a restaurant.”
It’s clear to me that the owner doesn’t think her employees deserve tips and as a hospitality employee and former barista, that indicates that she doesn’t care about her employees being recognized for delivering good service. There is no way she’s paying her employees enough that they wouldn’t appreciate a tip.
We would return for the food and service but would rather not put money in her pocket.

This review is overdue. I stopped by on Sunday, 02-05-23 while in the area. I ordered the passion fruit tart and the blue cheese pair danish. Both were good. I didn't try more because I thought it was a little pricey. The vibe was nice enough; not sure if it was more the staff, the inside guests, or both but there was a hint of being standoff-ish. Not sure I would return.
Excelente ambiente y el café espectacular al igual que la comida.

It has small seating inside but they do have a lot of tables and chairs outside. When the weather is nice would be perfect to sit outside, even the outside chairs give Paris vibes. Food was really good too!
Really beautiful decor, very Parisian vibe. Food was fresh and priced fairly. We will be back!
A little expensive,but very good testing,they have to do lattes less buble,I didn't have any drink :) I just huuped:)))
This place is so cute! I definitely want to visit again and actually dine-in. I got the Black Forest entremet & chocolate raspberry eclair and they were both superb.
Such a beautiful, French style cafe in Southpark Charlotte NC
The cutest little spot. Incredible service and the food was so good. Will definitely be coming back
Very welcoming, they were willing to stay over to accommodate or service. Very professional and clean. Definitely a place I would come back as a regular.
The latte was good.
Luogo raffinato, ottimo per una pausa caffè.

The patisserie is so beautiful and chic. The minuted we walked in we were greeted and a gentleman explained everything they had on the display.We ordered a coffee tart, pistachio Macaroon and pumpkin spice mousse cake (i guess that's what it was called).We also ordered Blue Matcha with almond milk which was just perfect.Everything was so perfect.I will back to satiate my craving for french dessert soon.
This place is quiant, and the pastry selection is perfect.  The homemade lavender comes close to the superb one at Chrmn Cafe, Elgin, Texas!

One of the best coffee in Charlotte. If you know how should taste good coffee this is a place to get one. As for macaroons unfortunately they were not fresh  :(
We tried another pastries - they were perfect

Pros: The cafe had a lovely atmosphere. The decor was very pretty and it was clean inside.

Cons: I saw a post of Chez Marie on Instagram and came here very excited to try it out, unfortunately it was a disappointment. I tried the Pumpkin Spice dessert and the Spinach and Feta Danish and both were very bland.  I was disappointed on the lack of flavor from both pastries and did not feel like they were worth the price.
We ordered Blue Matcha and Paris Brest and both were amazing. Couldn’t taste the savory stuff as it was very close to their closing time. But overall very good place.

By far The BEST PATISSERIE in Charlotte!!!!! The ingredients are really good and the place was so beautiful, there's outdoor and indoor seating. It's clean and open, love it! This place takes all the little details into consideration, they are not mass produced as some other bakeries. All their choices are delicious and nothing is too sweet that it can't be eaten. They also had a unique option for a decaf flower/tea latte. It was a blue color and tasted pretty good, complimenting the sweets perfectly. After trying all the patisseries in Charlotte this is our favorite and we will be back.
I didn't like the service, the sandwich came wrong, the espresso tasted burnt, I don't like to complain but I really wouldn't go back to this place

The atmosphere of the cafe was far from comfortable, and it felt as if the employees were just gathered there, maintaining an awkward silence throughout the visit. Overall, my experience at this cafe was less than satisfactory, I hope they can work on improving their service and ambiance in the future.

It’s simple at Chez Marie I found a piece of home. I’m from Paris, France and I have lived in the US for 10 years.
I have tried dozen of “French authentic” cafe & such and this one I can tell you is LEGIT !
The atmosphere, the music playing in the background and most importantly the QUALITY of the food was there !
We’ve tried the quiche Lorraine, chocolate croissant, blue cheese/pear danish and I wanted SO MUCH MORE.
Can’t recommend enough & will be back for sure !
A lovely place for your coffee/tea time. Service is ok, but the food and drinks are pretty good

It's a really nice place! Very nice style and unique delicious food.
Prices are good for the quality.
Super cute cafe, very clean. Friendly and fast service. Tasty pastries!

Je l'aime! The space is modern, a bit minimalisic but with a touch of elegance. I tried the passion fruit tart. Parfait! The right amount of sweetness. It was smooth and light. I would definitely go back to try the other pastries.

Chez Marie is a massive upgrade to the space and a welcome addition to SP.  The quality of the pastries is high and we can’t wait to try more things. We started with the 2 Entremets, Berry and Frazier. We also picked up Pain au Chocolate, Blue Cheese Pear Danish, Macarons and a Passion Fruit Tart.  On our next visit we’ll go for lunch and try the sandwiches and salads. CM is off to a great start.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemon Meringue Tart, Madeleine, Mousse Au Chocolat, Fraisier Entremet Mini

reviews_data.review_text: The best cafe in town. Friendly customer service. I highly recommend everyone to visit this place.I had an afternoon tea.  jasmine is so nice I had a great customer service.

Awe, I was so excited to try this place.  I ordered lunch to go today.  The Crepe Monsieur.  It's my favorite crepe anywhere.  Smoked ham, gruyere, bernaise sauce and a fried egg.  It was soooo disappointing.  I am not sure if they simply forgot, but there was no bernaise and gruyere on it.  It was just egg and ham and was super dry.  Without the sauce or cheese it just had no flavor.  I wish I had taken a picture of the inside but I ended up tossing it and wasting $15.  I hate leaving a bad review but feel like they need the feedback.  The store itself was cute and the service was fast and friendly.  I will likely give them one more try and check the crepe before I leave.  If it's better I will update my review
So delicious
YUM!!!

A place with plenty of ambiance and great service. Chez Marie sandwich was very tasty and almond croissant was perfect. I enjoyed my cappuccino and was glad it was served in a real cup. Will be back for more!

Десерти не можу назвати смачними чи свіжими, взагалі не насолодилася ними, єдине що було кафе на вигляд приємне а от ціни за такий смак не дуже.
Не Раджу Нікому.

A cute place in SouthPark area.
We went there Sunday afternoon and the shelves were half empty. My friend got macarons which were okay but nothing special.
I took the cardamom roll which was tasty! It has a creamy filling with cardamom flavor - more on the sweeter side though. Would love to come back and try new varieties.

They are open! Right now. We just decided to double check because Google maps say they are closed today.
Cappuccino is great! We got a bunch of desserts to go.
Bello exquisito única experiencia 😘
Lovely cafe, everything looked pristine inside. The treats I got were delicious but it do is a bit pricey. Staff was very friendly.
Pricey but great
Food was delicious 😋 Especially the atmosphere of the place made us feel like we were in France 🇫🇷
Dessert wasn't fresh

So impressed! I ordered an almond milk latte. The espresso was so smooth and not bitter at all. To eat, I ordered the crepe monsieur. It was topped with a fried egg, sunny side up, that had golden and slightly crisp edges. The yolk was not overly runny. The crepe was a nice balance of savory with a hint of sweetness and the dressing that came with the side salad was also very tasty. I will definitely be coming back.

Excellent coffee shop! I recommend the almond croissant and an oat milk cappuccino with vanilla. It’s always very clean and bright. Only gets busy in the middle of the day Saturday. I love stopping by Chez Marie!

What a lovely cafe! I was drawn in by the stunningly beautiful entremets (multiple flavor layers with gluten free cake, then  covered in a beautiful glaze). They are also available in full sized cakes like the Black Forest cake for my birthday (pictured).  I love to surprise my friends with these awesome tasting beauties. They always bring smiles!

My husband loves the croissants and danishes (sweet or savory) with coffee.  I am in love with the London Fog tea with oat milk and any gluten free treat (I rotate on the flavors).  My goddaughter loves the salads, a chai tea latte and the berry entremets. We love to sit in the fresh inside atmosphere or outdoors on a nice day.

Chez Marie makes my heart feel light. It always feels so cosmopolitan to hear snippets of British, Spanish or French accents. So worth a visit or for takeout!
It was very cute and nice cafe. It was kinda busy even I visit in around 10 AM in Sunday. They have various pastries and breads. Desserts was amazing too!
Came here after watching too much British Baking show. Was not disappointed. Love the tarts. I will keep coming back until my pants don’t fit.
Amazing desserts
A nice french bakery with very good and kind service. Good bread, cookies and pastries.
Very nice and cozy bakery Cafe with a nice choice of pretty and delicious pastries and other desserts.  I really enjoyed my time there with my girlfriends on my birthday.

This was one of the BEST lattes I’ve ever had! I got a vanilla iced oat milk latte & the espresso was so smooth. The girls at the front were super sweet as well. Highly recommend & will be back next time I’m in Charlotte!
Gorgeously cozy cafe. Wi-Fi is extremely fast. The pastries are absolutely beautiful.

I'm new to Charlotte and was looking for a cafe with a nice, elegant ambience and pastries. Finally found it at Chez Marie Patisserie. My Argentine husband says it's the best pastry he's had in the U.S! Very fresh, delicious croissants and coffee.
They have the best croissants and pain au chocolat I've ever had in the US.
Good coffe, tasty deserts & cozy atmosphere
A more specialized selection of goods which is always fun. Employee was pleasant & the macaron had a good texture.

Great patisserie / cafe. Been here several times now. Food is elegantly presented. French music to give the vibe. Taste is spot on - I’ve tried croissant, eclair, and more as well as sandwiches/quiche. All excellent. A bit tucked away but worth looking for. Owners are kind people too.

reviews_data.review_text: A little pricey but excellent pastries which I would pay a premium for. It's located in a pretty busy area and there isn't much space inside the cafe.  Worth a visit at least once.
Their pastries are always amazing!
My absolute favorite thing about Paris were the pastries and I've been trying to find something comparable here in Charlotte and this was it. A bit expensive but everything has been so good!

The girls were nice, friendly, beautiful- wanted to ask one of them out but was scared :( came with my friends ate outside- they came brought our food and took the dishes away- good place but very small- they need to make it bigger.
Excellent place to enjoy the atmosphere and the delicious french patisserie! 5Stars!
I need this place in my life!
Delicious and super authentic! The staff and owner are a delight to speak with. Wow- everything was so great and decadent.
While on the pricier side, you cannot beat it here. I have never had an item disappoint. Excellent staff and service.
I have a blue cheese pear danish THAT WAS AMAZING. The coffee was pretty good and everyone was VERY NICE. We were 7 and a baby and have a great time.

Always the perfect experience when looking to enjoy a coffee in an adorable environment. Reading a book, working remotely, or just people watching, the environment invites the customer to stay a while and enjoy!

Maravilloso sitio para compartir el té de lavanda espectacular, todos los postres que probamos Deliciosos… Gracias por crear este lugar  tan acogedor.
La música estaba un poco alta de volumen sin embargo la melodía magnífica, su dueño muy amable y sonriente atento para saber cómo la estábamos pasando ( Importante Detalle)

Place is cozy and nicely decorated. Staff was welcoming!
A bit disappointed in the lack of variety in the pastries, I may have been too used to French patisseries (mille feuille, religieuse...etc) but like the owner said to previous reviews there is always room for improvement.
The pastries are delicious!
Will def go back!
Chocolate raspberry eclair
Absolutely Amazing! Reminds me of being in Europe and truly a gem!!

I went there to grab a few snacks for the office and was pleasantly surprised by how friendly everyone was there.  At first I was overwhelmed by the selection but after talking to the staff I was able to get a great assortment of stuff.  The whole office loved what I picked out!

Very great experience with the variety of desserts and sandwiches. The almond croissant is to die for, I could eat 3 of them at a time if I could.  The staff are very knowledgeable of the items and always greet you when you enter. The place is also exceptionally clean. Definitely try this place out!

Every time I’ve been to Chez Marie, I am always greeted by multiple staff. The layout of the cafe is beautiful and gives a very European vibe for Charlotte. The staff answer any questions I have about the food. I am not used to some of the desserts but the staff always take time  to explain what each one is. I have tried multiple desserts as well as sandwiches and have enjoyed every item I’ve tasted.  If you’re ever in the South Park area, I highly recommend checking it out!

Did management change? I typically go once or twice a week to get pastries here. They are typically amazing. Yesterday the pain au chocolate was hard, very stale, not buttery and just looked different (I visited at 8:30am). I didn't even finish my pastry and threw the others that I had purchased out.

What a delightful find. The atmosphere is simple and Chic. The French music made me smile the whole time. Our Cappuccino and London fog were perfect. My almond croissant was scrumptious. We also had Berry danish was good. The Crepe monsieur was delicious and light. Only drawback was my quiche Lorraine. The taste was on part but the crust under the eggs was raw. If the quiche was cooked properly this would of been a 10/10!
I live the details, feel in Paris again.
Such a lovely place.  Team was very welcoming and patiently walked through the options.  Will certainly stop here again!
A must try! The pastries are not only absolutely stunning, they taste incredible! We cannot wait to come visit again for more!
Awesome pastries!

Such a cute place but not really “open”at 8. The steamer wasn’t working, so no cappuccino, the quiches and hot food isn’t ready until 9, and overall the service felt like they were annoyed to have a customer actually come in around opening. Not a great time but maybe it’s better after 10am?
Outstanding dessert menu and service!

Tastefully executed Parisian inspired atmosphere.  Far less of a pastry variety than the other well known French pastry shop in town but this is for a reason.  This isn’t a premade heat and sell shop.  This is a make from scratch attention to detail shop.  Beautiful product and lovely, welcoming staff. When friends and family come from Europe to visit we take them here for an espresso and pastry. Quality is evident and this is downright the most authentic experience in Charlotte. Period.

The staff treated us with kindness and attention, even though we were sneaking in right before close. We felt as if we were their first customers of the day. They made helpful suggestions and the pastries were incredibly high quality. I’m so glad we decided to try all four flavors of the Macarons. 100% worth it.

This is a phenomenal bakery in the area. The cafe itself is in pristine condition, a nice variety of desserts and coffees. Staff is wonderful! Definitely a great place to check out for your sweet cravings!
Lovely  place!
Очень вкусно!!!
Cute shop for coffee. High end.
Fancy and tasty.
Outstanding!

Got the mushroom pastry, a lemon tart,, and hot chocolate... The mushroom was one of the best things I've ever eaten, and I had just gotten back from eating at fancy dessert places in Las Vegas by famous chefs. Prices were justified in my opinion. Very delicious!

Gorgeous is an understatement! From the drinks, to the pastries, to the food this place is STUNNING! Upscale coffee shop, great for a ladies lunch or working remote, the music is a calm French vibe. Everything I had is delicious and the staff are kind, attentive, and lovely!
amazing macaroons and passion fruit tart!!!

Those pastries and dessert look stunning and taste delicious. I ordered a regular croissant, almond croissant and chocolate croissant, berry mousse cake, a coffee éclair and a hazelnut cream pastry to share on my way to Asheville. However the staff forgot my regular croissant which was so disappointing. When we found out we were in Asheville and we couldn’t go back. We wish when it comes with a large order, staffs could have paid attention to details.

Absolutely outstanding. From the food quality, to presentation, to service, to atmosphere and cleanliness of the place. What a treat, all of it! The people who work here treat us in a way that makes us feel like royalty every time we come. The pastries are phenomenal, so much better than most bakeries - AND most upscale restaurant desserts! Also, the espresso drinks are excellent. Lastly: delicious gluten free choices! And lovely French music playing in the background. We'll keep coming back!
The assorted pastries were delectable and beautiful. All the ladies enjoyed and I know you will be getting orders from them.

We stopped in for a late breakfast ordering a  Blue Matcha with almond milk -yum! one blue cheese macaron, one pistachio, and one passion fruit- all very fresh. The show stopper was the blue cheese pear danish..oh my!!! Can’t wait to return 👏🏻🇫🇷✨
The raspberry entremet was wonderful, great texture and flavors. The Madeleines  were kind of dry on the inside but had good flavor. I think they're worth another shot.

Beautiful and delicious pastries! Coffee was spectacular too, and the staff is lovely.  The tables out front reminds me of the patisseries I visited in France! I will definitely be back to try the sandwiches.
Amazing pastries!

Now, the service was pleasant. The pastries were not. I got the mango tart, which ended up being $8... It was hard and flavorless, tasted nothing like a mango. My mom got some lavender cake, that was hard like cornbread. A little pricey for pastries like that...

A delight from a moment we entered Chez Marie!  The decor was fresh with an understated elegance. The pastries were a work of art and our only disappointment was not being able to taste more of the offerings. We look forward to indulging ourselves with many visits.
What a marvelous cafe. The pastries were presented as if they were art pieces, and tasted very good. Can't wait to go back.

I stopped in yesterday was so impressed,
Great choices, pastries absolutely beautiful.
Super friendly and Welcoming Staff.
Very Clean.
The mint lemonade and Salted Carmel so yummy.      Will be back

A taste of Paris here in Charlotte !

Chez Marie is a French bakery located in the South Park area .

They have all types of pastries, savory sandwiches, specialty lattes,teas and more . Super cute in the inside and my two absolute favorites was the blue matcha latte and the almond croissant . Oh my gosh the almond croissant I can’t stop bragging about specifically. I also ordered a pistachio eclair that was tasty as well but not my favorite I think I could have lived with out the extra filling inside .

Definitely a cute bakery nestled in a shopping area you should grab your girls or a date and go check them out .

Had the quiche Provençal, bought a sourdough loaf and an almond croissant.  The bread and pastry were amazing!  The quiche was flavorful, a little dense/flat compared to what I’m used to, but it was the smallest, tiniest piece I’ve ever seen. Will not make a dent in your hunger. If they are get portion size figured out, we’d get it again. If not, it’s way overpriced, you would need to buy two.

reviews_data.review_text: This is still my favorite French/European cafe style place in Charlotte. The quality is always consistent, everyone working is very nice and pricing is not outrageous. They also have savory options if you’re wanting a light lunch or snack outside of the sweets.
We had some beautiful lattes at Chez Marie. Their macarons were also very fresh. We sat outside on an early Saturday morning, so not too much noise or traffic. We will definitely be back.

Wonderful atmosphere, feels like you’re in Europe. Staff were very friendly and greeted us and if we had any questions on the menu.
Started off with the Blue chai latte which was absolutely delicious, not too overpowering, just right.
The deserts were top tier treats. The Coconut mojito is packed with coconut and lime flavors. Very moist cake inside with a coconut moose jello like outer ring, topped with white chocolate. The Passion fruit cheesecake has a soft cheesecake texture with a big passion fruit flavor.
The Quiche Loraine had smoky ham pieces inside alongside a delicious gooey cheese. The only thing I would change is the crust because it was a bit too thick. The Le Picque-Nique had all fresh ingredients. A Crunchy toasted baguette with smoked ham and beautifully blended toppings. Doesn’t get any fresher than that.
Overall, Perfect spot for couples and a girls brunch or lunch. Definitely check them out!!!

Excelentes.
Super amables y delicioso.
Absolutely amazing authentic pastries, if you haven't been you must try it and if you've tried it I know you're going back again

reviews_data.review_text: The sandwich with Brie cheese is my favorite! Such a great spot for afternoon tea in CLT
I loved it, I recommend it
I love it here! Excellent service, will be coming back soon
I love the desserts here. All the food is delicious. They also have excellent service... highly recommended!

An amazing spot!
Has delicious desserts and cakes 👏🏼
Beautiful place and good service

I went today with my family and the attention was incredible, the atmosphere very pleasant, the staff very attentive. I loved the variety of options they had. I recommend the Pain chocolate and the pistachio paris brest are the best I've tried!

This place has terrible customer service. Beware if you are doing the afternoon tea that they will not accommodate dietary restrictions nor tell you what you will be getting. A member of our party has a severe nut allergy and informed the staff before she paid and was assured they would accommodate her. However, all food arrived together with many items with nuts. Nut free items were touching any items she could possibly eat. She requested to pay only for her tea since she could no longer have the food and was told no. The manager was very combative to talk to and it took a significant amount of effort to be able to receive a refund (the manager told us it was our fault for not mentioning allergies and that any allergies we had were our responsibility—however the staff was told about allergies beforehand and still charged and ignored information that was provided beforehand) I would not recommend going here—the service is terrible and the food is below average for what you are paying for. There are much better cafes to spend your time and money in Charlotte with much better service.
My favorite cafe in town. Coffee is consistently good, pastries are superb and service is always friendly.

I was extremely disappointed in the service that my friend and I received when visiting this establishment. Immediately upon walking in we were not greeted or acknowledged in any way, shape or form. Which was a bit of a red flag, being that we found out about this place via TikTok and were super excited to visit. We still proceeded to the counter, which had 3 people in front of us (who looked as though they were in the same party). As we walked up to the counter and looked around for a paper menu, the workers still did not acknowledge our presence or say that they would be with us. This was another huge red flag after waiting for about 5 minutes to not only be acknowledged, but also assisted, we ended up leaving. We have no intention of ever coming back to this establishment.
Amazing experience. We bought many items and they were all mind blowing. The staff went above and beyond what we expected.
Cute little coffee shop with sweet pastries. Get there early, they sell out. Cute vibe to hang out or work.
Love this place!!!
ok pastry. not enough variety to choose from

Pastries were absolutely amazing. Coconut mojito mousse cake was out of this world. Berry Entremet was so silky and smooth. Service was okay. No one smiling or greeting but you could tell they were under stress. The atmosphere was very off and unpleasant. Chez Marie is very small shop and there is not much space, but the issue is the energy inside the building. I was so anxious. The customers inside were being so rude to the employees and honestly it really ruined the experience for me. Would go back for the pastries.
Very good pastries.  Well executed. Expensive but nice little date or meet with friends spot.
Picked up a passion fruit tart for my wife for her birthday. It’s her favorite ! It’s a distance to go there but well worth it.

Chez Marie is the cutest bakery ever. The atmosphere is sophisticated but also calm and sweet. The mixed berry danish, Madelines and chai latte are my favorites. The staff is always super nice. I definitely recommend for a coffee date with friends !

reviews_data.review_text: Very lovely place. Great pâtisseries and atmosphere

This is a lovely bakery! It’s so bright and clean and welcoming. The pastries are very good. Sometimes you see something and you think, oh, it’ll be ok and it is. This was not one of those times! I chose a ham and cheese croissant. It was not the biggest or showiest pastry, but it was delicious. (Going to show me not to judge a book by its cover!) I took it to go, but it was so cute inside, it looked like a nice place to meet a friend or to work for a little bit.

I’ve been torn about posting this—part of me wants to give it 5 stars because it’s that good, but the other part wants to keep it a hidden gem. Selfishly, I’d rather not blow up the spot… but here we go.  Everything is amazing - trust me - I’ve tried it all.

Went 3 times within 2 days!
I loved the calm and classy atmosphere of this place. Tried the regular latte and ice latte, also their croissants, everything was very good.
The music selection is perfect for sitting and enjoying a good coffee by yourself of with company, sitting in a comfortable and yet beautiful couch.
The service was fantastic, everyone was nice and friendly every time I went.

I really like the pastries here but they’ve gotten lazy over the years. They used to have new items what seemed to be every week and they had much more variety of breads and pastries. Now it is rather baron in there

Beautiful, charming and simply delightful cafe w/ amazing authentic French desserts! Every bite was pure bliss! Drinks were strong and delicious as well.

I was in a hurry, and didn’t pay much attention to the bill. When I got home, I checked my ApplePay and noticed they had cost $33 (~$8/pastry). I thought that was a bit expensive, and checked the website, where they were listed as $3.50 each. Even with a generous tip, I was charged about  $10 extra. I assumed it must have been a simple mistake, and went back ten minutes later. I explained the situation to the lady who had just checked me out. None of the ladies behind the counter seemed to speak much English, ( and didn’t respond to my Spanish) and told me the owner who I had chatted with 10 min prior was gone. Chez Marie is a pretty solid French Patisserie. I got the opportunity to taste a large variety of the pastries they were selling that day and was impressed for the most part. The mixed berry entremet was my favorite thing that I tried: it was tart, light, and rich at the same time, while not being overly sweet. The chocolate entremet, while having a pretty presentation, was way too rich and was difficult to eat more than a couple of nibbles. The lemon tart was also pretty with the toasted meringue on it, however, it tasted a little too much like a key lime pie to me. All of the macaroons that I tried were good as well, with standouts being the raspberry and pistachio. The location is very nice in South Park near the OG Pancake House and has a pretty, delicate interior. The ladies working the front were also very nice. It seems they change what they are selling often, I will have to go back and check it out again sometime.
Pretty limited option and they were out of quite a few things by 12:30 on a weekday.

A great spot to feel like you’ve traveled outside of the states! Great atmosphere, beautiful and delicious pastries and coffee, and clean 👌 We ordered the pistachio French best, Black Forest emberet, and a vanilla latte. Everything was excellent! Definitely was not expecting this!   Traveling from far away seen this advertised from IG influencer. Everything looked great.  Surprised at how small it was inside. It’s very small and intimate in there and not much seating but fortunately we were able to find some once a group left. I ordered the London fog, smoked ham sandwich and a cheese danish. I was very excited to go there to eat, I read several reviews of the place and it is just as described, a very nice atmosphere and good customer service and the food was delicious, I hope to go there again with my friends!
The place is very nice,even though I did not stay.The Pastries are very good.

Great place! I recently had the pleasure of dining at Chez Marie Patisserie, and it was a delightful experience! The moment I walked in, I was greeted by the heavenly aroma of freshly baked goods and the charming, cozy atmosphere. I started with a buttery croissant that was perfectly flaky and golden. For dessert, I couldn’t resist trying their signature macarons, which were exquisite—soft, colorful, and filled with rich flavors. I also enjoyed a slice of their decadent chocolate cake, which was rich and moist, a true indulgence. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, eager to help with recommendations. Overall, Chez Marie Patisserie is a must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth or looking for a cozy spot to enjoy delicious pastries. I can't wait to go back and try more of their delectable treats!

reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are sorry you were dissatisfied with your experience at Chez Marie.

We believe that the value of our products that we offer is fairly estimated and it corresponds to the high quality of the ingredients we select and hard work we apply. 

We agree with your comment about the design on the latte, but we are currently training new people. We can reassure you that the quality of the drink remains the same as all of our baristas follow the same recipe. 

We wanted to make it right to you and served you a freshly made cappuccino upon your request free of charge, that you have also asked to be taken “to go”.

We make all our desserts daily and due to a high demand we run out of many items by the end of the day. Our customers can always call and place an advance order for a later pick up.

This place takes all the little details into consideration, they are not mass produced as some other bakeries. All their choices are delicious and nothing is too sweet that it can't be eaten. They also had a unique option for a decaf flower/tea latte. It was a blue color and tasted pretty good, complimenting the sweets perfectly. After trying all the patisseries in Charlotte this is our favorite and we will be back.
I didn't like the service, the sandwich came wrong, the espresso tasted burnt, I don't like to complain but I really wouldn't go back to this place

The atmosphere of the cafe was far from comfortable, and it felt as if the employees were just gathered there, maintaining an awkward silence throughout the visit. Overall, my experience at this cafe was less than satisfactory, I hope they can work on improving their service and ambiance in the future.

It’s simple at Chez Marie I found a piece of home. I’m from Paris, France and I have lived in the US for 10 years.
I have tried dozen of “French authentic” cafe & such and this one I can tell you is LEGIT !
The atmosphere, the music playing in the background and most importantly the QUALITY of the food was there !
We’ve tried the quiche Lorraine, chocolate croissant, blue cheese/pear danish and I wanted SO MUCH MORE.
Can’t recommend enough & will be back for sure !
A lovely place for your coffee/tea time. Service is ok, but the food and drinks are pretty good

It's a really nice place! Very nice style and unique delicious food.
Prices are good for the quality.
Super cute cafe, very clean. Friendly and fast service. Tasty pastries!

Je l'aime! The space is modern, a bit minimalisic but with a touch of elegance. I tried the passion fruit tart. Parfait! The right amount of sweetness. It was smooth and light. I would definitely go back to try the other pastries.

Chez Marie is a massive upgrade to the space and a welcome addition to SP.  The quality of the pastries is high and we can’t wait to try more things. We started with the 2 Entremets, Berry and Frazier. We also picked up Pain au Chocolate, Blue Cheese Pear Danish, Macarons and a Passion Fruit Tart.  On our next visit we’ll go for lunch and try the sandwiches and salads. CM is off to a great start.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemon Meringue Tart, Madeleine, Mousse Au Chocolat, Fraisier Entremet Mini

reviews_data.review_text: The best cafe in town. Friendly customer service. I highly recommend everyone to visit this place.I had an afternoon tea.  jasmine is so nice I had a great customer service.

Awe, I was so excited to try this place.  I ordered lunch to go today.  The Crepe Monsieur.  It's my favorite crepe anywhere.  Smoked ham, gruyere, bernaise sauce and a fried egg.  It was soooo disappointing.  I am not sure if they simply forgot, but there was no bernaise and gruyere on it.  It was just egg and ham and was super dry.  Without the sauce or cheese it just had no flavor.  I wish I had taken a picture of the inside but I ended up tossing it and wasting $15.  I hate leaving a bad review but feel like they need the feedback.  The store itself was cute and the service was fast and friendly.  I will likely give them one more try and check the crepe before I leave.  If it's better I will update my review
So delicious
YUM!!!

A place with plenty of ambiance and great service. Chez Marie sandwich was very tasty and almond croissant was perfect. I enjoyed my cappuccino and was glad it was served in a real cup. Will be back for more!

Десерти не можу назвати смачними чи свіжими, взагалі не насолодилася ними, єдине що було кафе на вигляд приємне а от ціни за такий смак не дуже.
Не Раджу Нікому.

A cute place in SouthPark area.
We went there Sunday afternoon and the shelves were half empty. My friend got macarons which were okay but nothing special.
I took the cardamom roll which was tasty! It has a creamy filling with cardamom flavor - more on the sweeter side though. Would love to come back and try new varieties.

They are open! Right now. We just decided to double check because Google maps say they are closed today.
Cappuccino is great! We got a bunch of desserts to go.
Bello exquisito única experiencia 😘
Lovely cafe, everything looked pristine inside. The treats I got were delicious but it do is a bit pricey. Staff was very friendly.
Pricey but great
Food was delicious 😋 Especially the atmosphere of the place made us feel like we were in France 🇫🇷
Dessert wasn't fresh

So impressed! I ordered an almond milk latte. The espresso was so smooth and not bitter at all. To eat, I ordered the crepe monsieur. It was topped with a fried egg, sunny side up, that had golden and slightly crisp edges. The yolk was not overly runny. The crepe was a nice balance of savory with a hint of sweetness and the dressing that came with the side salad was also very tasty. I will definitely be coming back.

Excellent coffee shop! I recommend the almond croissant and an oat milk cappuccino with vanilla. It’s always very clean and bright. Only gets busy in the middle of the day Saturday. I love stopping by Chez Marie!

What a lovely cafe! I was drawn in by the stunningly beautiful entremets (multiple flavor layers with gluten free cake, then  covered in a beautiful glaze). They are also available in full sized cakes like the Black Forest cake for my birthday (pictured).  I love to surprise my friends with these awesome tasting beauties. They always bring smiles!

My husband loves the croissants and danishes (sweet or savory) with coffee.  I am in love with the London Fog tea with oat milk and any gluten free treat (I rotate on the flavors).  My goddaughter loves the salads, a chai tea latte and the berry entremets. We love to sit in the fresh inside atmosphere or outdoors on a nice day.

Chez Marie makes my heart feel light. It always feels so cosmopolitan to hear snippets of British, Spanish or French accents. So worth a visit or for takeout!
It was very cute and nice cafe. It was kinda busy even I visit in around 10 AM in Sunday. They have various pastries and breads. Desserts was amazing too!
Came here after watching too much British Baking show. Was not disappointed. Love the tarts. I will keep coming back until my pants don’t fit.
Amazing desserts
A nice french bakery with very good and kind service. Good bread, cookies and pastries.
Very nice and cozy bakery Cafe with a nice choice of pretty and delicious pastries and other desserts.  I really enjoyed my time there with my girlfriends on my birthday.

This was one of the BEST lattes I’ve ever had! I got a vanilla iced oat milk latte & the espresso was so smooth. The girls at the front were super sweet as well. Highly recommend & will be back next time I’m in Charlotte!
Gorgeously cozy cafe. Wi-Fi is extremely fast. The pastries are absolutely beautiful.

I'm new to Charlotte and was looking for a cafe with a nice, elegant ambience and pastries. Finally found it at Chez Marie Patisserie. My Argentine husband says it's the best pastry he's had in the U.S! Very fresh, delicious croissants and coffee.
They have the best croissants and pain au chocolat I've ever had in the US.
Good coffe, tasty deserts & cozy atmosphere
A more specialized selection of goods which is always fun. Employee was pleasant & the macaron had a good texture.

Great patisserie / cafe. Been here several times now. Food is elegantly presented. French music to give the vibe. Taste is spot on - I’ve tried croissant, eclair, and more as well as sandwiches/quiche. All excellent. A bit tucked away but worth looking for. Owners are kind people too.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Quiche, Ham and Gruyere Cheese Sandwich

reviews_data.review_text: A little pricey but excellent pastries which I would pay a premium for. It's located in a pretty busy area and there isn't much space inside the cafe.  Worth a visit at least once.
Their pastries are always amazing!
My absolute favorite thing about Paris were the pastries and I've been trying to find something comparable here in Charlotte and this was it. A bit expensive but everything has been so good!

The girls were nice, friendly, beautiful- wanted to ask one of them out but was scared :( came with my friends ate outside- they came brought our food and took the dishes away- good place but very small- they need to make it bigger.
Excellent place to enjoy the atmosphere and the delicious french patisserie! 5Stars!
I need this place in my life!
Delicious and super authentic! The staff and owner are a delight to speak with. Wow- everything was so great and decadent.
While on the pricier side, you cannot beat it here. I have never had an item disappoint. Excellent staff and service.
I have a blue cheese pear danish THAT WAS AMAZING. The coffee was pretty good and everyone was VERY NICE. We were 7 and a baby and have a great time.

Always the perfect experience when looking to enjoy a coffee in an adorable environment. Reading a book, working remotely, or just people watching, the environment invites the customer to stay a while and enjoy!

Maravilloso sitio para compartir el té de lavanda espectacular, todos los postres que probamos Deliciosos… Gracias por crear este lugar  tan acogedor.
La música estaba un poco alta de volumen sin embargo la melodía magnífica, su dueño muy amable y sonriente atento para saber cómo la estábamos pasando ( Importante Detalle)

Place is cozy and nicely decorated. Staff was welcoming!
A bit disappointed in the lack of variety in the pastries, I may have been too used to French patisseries (mille feuille, religieuse...etc) but like the owner said to previous reviews there is always room for improvement.
The pastries are delicious!
Will def go back!
Chocolate raspberry eclair
Absolutely Amazing! Reminds me of being in Europe and truly a gem!!

I went there to grab a few snacks for the office and was pleasantly surprised by how friendly everyone was there.  At first I was overwhelmed by the selection but after talking to the staff I was able to get a great assortment of stuff.  The whole office loved what I picked out!

Very great experience with the variety of desserts and sandwiches. The almond croissant is to die for, I could eat 3 of them at a time if I could.  The staff are very knowledgeable of the items and always greet you when you enter. The place is also exceptionally clean. Definitely try this place out!

Every time I’ve been to Chez Marie, I am always greeted by multiple staff. The layout of the cafe is beautiful and gives a very European vibe for Charlotte. The staff answer any questions I have about the food. I am not used to some of the desserts but the staff always take time  to explain what each one is. I have tried multiple desserts as well as sandwiches and have enjoyed every item I’ve tasted.  If you’re ever in the South Park area, I highly recommend checking it out!

Did management change? I typically go once or twice a week to get pastries here. They are typically amazing. Yesterday the pain au chocolate was hard, very stale, not buttery and just looked different (I visited at 8:30am). I didn't even finish my pastry and threw the others that I had purchased out.

What a delightful find. The atmosphere is simple and Chic. The French music made me smile the whole time. Our Cappuccino and London fog were perfect. My almond croissant was scrumptious. We also had Berry danish was good. The Crepe monsieur was delicious and light. Only drawback was my quiche Lorraine. The taste was on part but the crust under the eggs was raw. If the quiche was cooked properly this would of been a 10/10!
I live the details, feel in Paris again.
Such a lovely place.  Team was very welcoming and patiently walked through the options.  Will certainly stop here again!
A must try! The pastries are not only absolutely stunning, they taste incredible! We cannot wait to come visit again for more!
Awesome pastries!

Such a cute place but not really “open”at 8. The steamer wasn’t working, so no cappuccino, the quiches and hot food isn’t ready until 9, and overall the service felt like they were annoyed to have a customer actually come in around opening. Not a great time but maybe it’s better after 10am?
Outstanding dessert menu and service!

Tastefully executed Parisian inspired atmosphere.  Far less of a pastry variety than the other well known French pastry shop in town but this is for a reason.  This isn’t a premade heat and sell shop.  This is a make from scratch attention to detail shop.  Beautiful product and lovely, welcoming staff. When friends and family come from Europe to visit we take them here for an espresso and pastry. Quality is evident and this is downright the most authentic experience in Charlotte. Period.

The staff treated us with kindness and attention, even though we were sneaking in right before close. We felt as if we were their first customers of the day. They made helpful suggestions and the pastries were incredibly high quality. I’m so glad we decided to try all four flavors of the Macarons. 100% worth it.

This is a phenomenal bakery in the area. The cafe itself is in pristine condition, a nice variety of desserts and coffees. Staff is wonderful! Definitely a great place to check out for your sweet cravings!
Lovely  place!
Очень вкусно!!!
Cute shop for coffee. High end.
Fancy and tasty.
Outstanding!

Got the mushroom pastry, a lemon tart,, and hot chocolate... The mushroom was one of the best things I've ever eaten, and I had just gotten back from eating at fancy dessert places in Las Vegas by famous chefs. Prices were justified in my opinion. Very delicious!

Gorgeous is an understatement! From the drinks, to the pastries, to the food this place is STUNNING! Upscale coffee shop, great for a ladies lunch or working remote, the music is a calm French vibe. Everything I had is delicious and the staff are kind, attentive, and lovely!
amazing macaroons and passion fruit tart!!!

Those pastries and dessert look stunning and taste delicious. I ordered a regular croissant, almond croissant and chocolate croissant, berry mousse cake, a coffee éclair and a hazelnut cream pastry to share on my way to Asheville. However the staff forgot my regular croissant which was so disappointing. When we found out we were in Asheville and we couldn’t go back. We wish when it comes with a large order, staffs could have paid attention to details.

Absolutely outstanding. From the food quality, to presentation, to service, to atmosphere and cleanliness of the place. What a treat, all of it! The people who work here treat us in a way that makes us feel like royalty every time we come. The pastries are phenomenal, so much better than most bakeries - AND most upscale restaurant desserts! Also, the espresso drinks are excellent. Lastly: delicious gluten free choices! And lovely French music playing in the background. We'll keep coming back!
The assorted pastries were delectable and beautiful. All the ladies enjoyed and I know you will be getting orders from them.

We stopped in for a late breakfast ordering a  Blue Matcha with almond milk -yum! one blue cheese macaron, one pistachio, and one passion fruit- all very fresh. The show stopper was the blue cheese pear danish..oh my!!! Can’t wait to return 👏🏻🇫🇷✨
The raspberry entremet was wonderful, great texture and flavors. The Madeleines  were kind of dry on the inside but had good flavor. I think they're worth another shot.

Beautiful and delicious pastries! Coffee was spectacular too, and the staff is lovely.  The tables out front reminds me of the patisseries I visited in France! I will definitely be back to try the sandwiches.
Amazing pastries!

Now, the service was pleasant. The pastries were not. I got the mango tart, which ended up being $8... It was hard and flavorless, tasted nothing like a mango. My mom got some lavender cake, that was hard like cornbread. A little pricey for pastries like that...

A delight from a moment we entered Chez Marie!  The decor was fresh with an understated elegance. The pastries were a work of art and our only disappointment was not being able to taste more of the offerings. We look forward to indulging ourselves with many visits.
What a marvelous cafe. The pastries were presented as if they were art pieces, and tasted very good. Can't wait to go back.

I stopped in yesterday was so impressed,
Great choices, pastries absolutely beautiful.
Super friendly and Welcoming Staff.
Very Clean.
The mint lemonade and Salted Carmel so yummy.      Will be back

A taste of Paris here in Charlotte !

Chez Marie is a French bakery located in the South Park area .

They have all types of pastries, savory sandwiches, specialty lattes,teas and more . Super cute in the inside and my two absolute favorites was the blue matcha latte and the almond croissant . Oh my gosh the almond croissant I can’t stop bragging about specifically. I also ordered a pistachio eclair that was tasty as well but not my favorite I think I could have lived with out the extra filling inside .

Definitely a cute bakery nestled in a shopping area you should grab your girls or a date and go check them out .

Had the quiche Provençal, bought a sourdough loaf and an almond croissant.  The bread and pastry were amazing!  The quiche was flavorful, a little dense/flat compared to what I’m used to, but it was the smallest, tiniest piece I’ve ever seen. Will not make a dent in your hunger. If they are get portion size figured out, we’d get it again. If not, it’s way overpriced, you would need to buy two.
